---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Contribute to Claudia">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="pt-24 pb-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-paper mb-6">
        The easiest open source contribution you'll ever make
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-paper/60 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Contributing to Claudia means writing markdown. No code review, no tests, no build step.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Contribution Types -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-paper mb-10 text-center">
        Pick your level
      </h2>
      <div class="grid gap-4">
        <!-- Card 1 -->
        <div class="group border border-soft-gray rounded-lg p-6 hover:border-vermillion/50 transition-colors">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 mb-2">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-paper">Add a reference file</h3>
            <span class="shrink-0 text-sm font-mono text-signal bg-signal/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded">
              ~30 min
            </span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-paper/50">
            Drop a <code class="text-vermillion/80">.md</code> in any <code class="text-vermillion/80">references/</code> directory. Write what you know about a technology, pattern, or best practice.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 2 -->
        <div class="group border border-soft-gray rounded-lg p-6 hover:border-vermillion/50 transition-colors">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 mb-2">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-paper">Add anti-pattern rules</h3>
            <span class="shrink-0 text-sm font-mono text-signal bg-signal/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded">
              ~1 hour
            </span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-paper/50">
            Add entries to hook scripts. Teach Claudia to catch common mistakes before they land.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 3 -->
        <div class="group border border-soft-gray rounded-lg p-6 hover:border-vermillion/50 transition-colors">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 mb-2">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-paper">Improve a domain</h3>
            <span class="shrink-0 text-sm font-mono text-signal bg-signal/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded">
              ~2 hours
            </span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-paper/50">
            Expand <code class="text-vermillion/80">SKILL.md</code> or add reference files to an existing knowledge domain.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 4 -->
        <div class="group border border-soft-gray rounded-lg p-6 hover:border-vermillion/50 transition-colors">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 mb-2">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-paper">Create a new domain</h3>
            <span class="shrink-0 text-sm font-mono text-signal bg-signal/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded">
              ~4 hours
            </span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-paper/50">
            Use the scaffolding tool to create a full knowledge domain from scratch.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Card 5 -->
        <div class="group border border-soft-gray rounded-lg p-6 hover:border-vermillion/50 transition-colors">
          <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4 mb-2">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-paper">Build a new hook</h3>
            <span class="shrink-0 text-sm font-mono text-signal bg-signal/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded">
              ~4 hours
            </span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-paper/50">
            Write a <code class="text-vermillion/80">PreToolUse</code> script that automatically catches issues on every file write.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick Start -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6 bg-soft-gray/30">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-paper mb-8 text-center">
        Quick start
      </h2>
      <div class="bg-void border border-soft-gray rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-3 border-b border-soft-gray">
          <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-vermillion/40"></span>
          <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-signal/40"></span>
          <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-paper/20"></span>
        </div>
        <pre class="p-6 text-sm leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto"><code class="text-paper/80"><span class="text-signal">git clone</span> https://github.com/reganomalley/claudia.git
<span class="text-signal">cd</span> claudia
<span class="text-signal">./scripts/create-domain.sh</span> architecture
<span class="text-paper/40"># Edit skills/claudia-architecture/SKILL.md</span>
<span class="text-paper/40"># Add references in skills/claudia-architecture/references/</span></code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Writing Guidelines -->
  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-paper mb-10 text-center">
        Writing guidelines
      </h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="border border-soft-gray rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-vermillion mb-3">Be opinionated</h3>
          <p class="text-paper/50 text-sm">
            Claudia doesn't present options neutrally. She recommends the right tool for the job and explains why alternatives fall short.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-soft-gray rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-vermillion mb-3">Use decision trees and comparison tables</h3>
          <p class="text-paper/50 text-sm">
            Structured guidance is more useful than paragraphs of prose. Help the reader make a choice, not just understand the landscape.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-soft-gray rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-vermillion mb-3">Explain the "why"</h3>
          <p class="text-paper/50 text-sm">
            Don't just say what to do -- explain the reasoning. Developers trust advice more when they understand the tradeoffs behind it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-soft-gray rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-vermillion mb-3">Include "when NOT to use this"</h3>
          <p class="text-paper/50 text-sm">
            Every tool has limits. Documenting when something is the wrong choice builds credibility and saves real debugging time.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="sm:col-span-2 border border-soft-gray rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-vermillion mb-3">Keep SKILL.md under ~2000 words</h3>
          <p class="text-paper/50 text-sm">
            SKILL.md is loaded into Claude's context window. Keep it tight. Move deep dives, reference tables, and extended examples into the <code class="text-vermillion/80">references/</code> directory -- those are loaded on demand.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <a
        href="https://github.com/reganomalley/claudia"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-vermillion hover:bg-vermillion/90 text-paper font-semibold px-8 py-3 rounded-lg transition-colors"
      >
        View on GitHub
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14" />
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
